Foot-and-mouth disease, Kazakhstan
----------------------------------
Information received on 14 May 2013 from Dr Mereke Taitubayev, Chairman, Committee of veterinary control and supervision, Ministry of Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 11 May 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 13 May 2013
Report date: 13 May 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 14 May 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 21 Aug 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1
Village Akshoka, Akshokinsky, Urdzharsky, East Kazakhstan
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 May 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 900 / 40 / 0 / 40 / 0
Sheep & goats / 3165 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: lameness, painful lesions on the feet, drooling, nasal discharge, lesions and areas of whitening on the mouth which can develop into fluid-filled blisters on the tongue.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 900 / 40 / 0 / 40 / 0
Sheep & goats / 3165 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: quarantine started on 13 May 2013.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, zoning, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), no treatment of affected animals
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated
East Kazakhstan / Sheep & goats / 3165
East Kazakhstan / Cattle / 860
Measures to be applied: movement control inside the country

